Real Madrid host Paris Saint-Germain in the Champions League on Tuesday night. Zinedine Zidane’s men will be hoping to get maximum points and close the five-point gap between them and the Ligue 1 champions. Madrid are on also seeking revenge, after losing 3-0 to PSG in their first Group A game. Kick off is 9pm West African time. Tuesday, November 26
